## Additional Terms for Privacy and Security

### Privacy Commitment
FaceAuth is designed with privacy-first principles. By using this software:

1. All biometric data remains local to your device
2. No data is transmitted to external servers
3. Face embeddings are stored securely using industry-standard encryption
4. Users maintain full control over their biometric data

### Security Disclaimer
While FaceAuth implements security best practices:

1. This software is provided for educational and personal use
2. Users are responsible for ensuring compliance with local privacy laws
3. For production use, please conduct appropriate security audits
4. The authors are not liable for any security breaches or data loss

### Biometric Data Handling
Special considerations for biometric data:

1. Face embeddings are one-way mathematical representations
2. Original images are not stored by default
3. Users can delete all biometric data at any time
4. Data portability is supported through standard export functions

### Compliance Notes
This software may be subject to various regulations including:
- GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation)
- CCPA (California Consumer Privacy Act)
- BIPA (Biometric Information Privacy Acts)
- Local biometric privacy laws

Users are responsible for ensuring compliance with applicable regulations
in their jurisdiction.

